      <hedline>
        <hl1>A 12-Year-Old Boy, Killed in Gaza</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Adam Levine letter contends blame for violence in Jerusalem lies entirely on its perpetrators, the Palestinian rioters</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mideast Violence Continues to Rage; Death Toll Rises'' (front page, Oct. 1):</p>
        <p>You seem to place all the blame for the violence on Ariel Sharon and on Israeli soldiers. While Mr. Sharon's walk on the Temple Mount was quite provocative, the blame for violence lies entirely on its perpetrators, the Palestinian rioters.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mideast Violence Continues to Rage; Death Toll Rises'' (front page, Oct. 1):</p>
        <p>You seem to place all the blame for the violence on Ariel Sharon and on Israeli soldiers. While Mr. Sharon's walk on the Temple Mount was quite provocative, the blame for violence lies entirely on its perpetrators, the Palestinian rioters.</p>
        <p>For example, the reference to ''the storming of the Muslim religious site on Friday afternoon by heavily armed Israeli troops'' places the blame on the Israeli forces, rather than on the rioters who were brutally and maliciously throwing rocks down on worshipers at the Western Wall with the intent to terrorize, maim and kill. Let's not forget who is at fault in this situation: the Palestinian mob.</p>
        <p>ADAM LEVINE  Scarsdale, N.Y., Oct. 1, 2000</p>
      </block>
